Hosts and distribution . This species is associated with number of passeriform birds from several continents. Passeriformes ( Alaudidae ):
Eremopterix leucotis (Stanley)
[ type host] from South Africa ( Fain 1972 , 1994 ),
Calandrella cinerea (Gmelin)
from Botswana (
Bochkov & Klompen 2014 b
),
Calandrella rufescens (Vieillot)
and
Alauda arvensis Linnaeus
from Kazakhstan (
Bochkov & Klompen 2014 b
).

Passeriformes ( Fringillidae ):
Rhodospiza obsoleta ( Lichtenstein )
from Kirgizia (Fain et al . 1999 ),
Spinus tristis
(Linnaeus) from USA (Wyoming) and
Leucosticte arctoa (Pallas)
from Canada (British Columbia ) (
Bochkov & Klompen 2014 b
).

Passeriformes ( Turdidae ):
Turdus migratorius
Linnaeus from USA (various localities) and
Sialia sialis
from USA (Mississippi) (
Bochkov & Klompen 2014 b; present paper
);
Catharus minimus
[ new host ] from USA (Michigan) (present paper).

Passeriformes ( Passeridae ):
Passer domesticus (Linnaeus)
from Algeria and Kirghizia (Fain et al . 1999 ;
Bochkov & Klompen 2014 b
).

Passeriformes ( Cardinalidae ):
Cardinalis sinuatus Bonaparte
from USA (Texas) (
Bochkov & Klompen 2014 b
).
